result.execSummary:
The defendant Kevin D Strenke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Provide Sex Offender Info (Misd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(2)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Must follow all rules of Probation.

miscConds.notes:
Defendant may request expungement of the DNA sample under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4) by petitioning the Wisconsin Department of Justice. Expungement of DNA is NOT a court process. 
For information see:
http://www.doj.state.wi.us/dles/crime-labs/clb-forms.  Must provide DNA sample with no surcharge. 
Must complete sex offender treatment program and comply.
